17:29.727 --> 17:33.345
At the lack of the drivers' uniforms

17:37.610 --> 17:40.361
And at the office during the duration

17:40.529 --> 17:43.020
What a pleasure giving dictation

17:43.199 --> 17:45.950
It ain't so bad in the land of the free

17:46.118 --> 17:48.490
Being a dictator lik e me

17:53.583 --> 17:56.668
And when my lady and I go dining

17:56.836 --> 17:58.876
Though the menu's cloudy
There's a silver lining

17:59.464 --> 18:00.495
That's the one.

18:00.673 --> 18:03.081
A fellow just looks around the floor

18:03.259 --> 18:05.797
Who could ask for anything more?

18:05.970 --> 18:07.797
Who could ask for anything more?

18:08.347 --> 18:11.633
Who's complaining?
I'm not complaining

18:11.809 --> 18:16.020
The sacrifices are few

18:16.188 --> 18:19.272
- My shoes may not be leathery
- My pillow not so feathery

18:19.441 --> 18:21.232
My legs may be forgotten

18:21.401 --> 18:23.358
In cotton

18:23.654 --> 18:25.278
No complaining

18:25.447 --> 18:27.071
Through the campaigning

18:27.240 --> 18:30.905
I'll raise no hullabaloo

18:31.077 --> 18:32.868
My nails may lose their brilliancy

18:33.037 --> 18:35.077
But who cares what civilians see

18:35.248 --> 18:37.786
So long as they don't ration
My passion

18:37.959 --> 18:39.998
For you

18:42.797 --> 18:46.000
Good night. Happy kitchen.

18:47.051 --> 18:50.336
Good night. Happy office.

18:51.013 --> 18:52.804
Good ni...

18:56.309 --> 18:59.061
Good night. Happy taxi.

19:07.028 --> 19:10.231
Good night. Happy smoking.

19:13.743 --> 19:15.901
Have that girl come
and see me tomorrow.

19:16.078 --> 19:20.241
I'm glad you liked her. I thought she
was quite unusual-looking for a blond.

19:20.416 --> 19:22.325
No, the one with the red hair.

19:22.501 --> 19:26.368
Oh, the red hair. Oh, the red hair!

19:30.967 --> 19:32.759
I'll be in the study for calls.

19:32.927 --> 19:37.885
I don't know why you pay me if you
ignore my judgment. Stop whistling!

19:38.057 --> 19:42.386
I wear myself out, wading through
10,000 girls, and out of the 10,000...

19:42.562 --> 19:46.559
you choose a redheaded nervous
breakdown who specializes in sneezes.

19:46.732 --> 19:48.310
She told me so.

19:48.484 --> 19:52.066
That one isn't a girl, John.
She's a leaping thyroid.

19:52.863 --> 19:57.074
I don't believe I've been in a honky-tonk
place like McGuire's for 40 years.

19:57.242 --> 20:02.236
I don't know why I've saved this. Take a
look at it. You're interested in antiques.

20:04.374 --> 20:06.248
If we got her for our cover...

20:06.459 --> 20:09.330
- But, John, this is her.
- Who?

20:09.545 --> 20:11.787
The... The girl, the gland case.

20:12.131 --> 20:14.966
This program is dated 40 years ago.
How could it be?

20:15.176 --> 20:16.967
Well, it couldn't be, but it is.

20:18.804 --> 20:21.722
Forty years ago.

20:22.766 --> 20:28.140
The night I got this, I was sitting
in a box with Tony Pastor.

20:32.359 --> 20:35.313
She was the most beautiful thing
I'd ever seen.

20:35.820 --> 20:38.940
I fell in love with her
the minute I saw her.

20:42.577 --> 20:48.033
The fav ourite doesn't always win
No matter what the odds

20:48.207 --> 20:50.994
Since nobody knows
How they'll come in

20:51.168 --> 20:54.085
I leave it to the gods

20:54.254 --> 21:00.506
So wish me luck
Because I'm going to bet on

21:00.677 --> 21:03.631
A sentimental hunch

21:03.805 --> 21:10.472
My heart is suddenly set on

21:12.105 --> 21:15.438
Somehow, I'm sure I've found

21:15.608 --> 21:19.688
The sure thing in you

21:19.862 --> 21:22.531
Something within

21:23.324 --> 21:27.155
Tells me we'll win

21:27.327 --> 21:29.450
