Give me some lights. I'll murder them.

47:57.374 --> 48:01.668
Rusty, this happens to very few people.
Take care of it and treat it right.

48:01.837 --> 48:03.746
I beg your pardon.
Oh, here you are.

48:03.922 --> 48:07.172
I've been in the theatre many years,
and I've never seen...

48:07.342 --> 48:08.717
Excuse me, please.

48:08.885 --> 48:12.336
As I was saying, I've been in the
theatre a number of years and...

48:12.514 --> 48:17.009
- As I was saying, I've been in the theatre...
- I'm beginning to believe that.

48:17.268 --> 48:19.011
- Hello, Rusty.
- Hello, Mr. Coudair.

48:19.187 --> 48:21.559
Hello, Miss Jackson.
Danny, these are...

48:21.731 --> 48:24.400
- Well, this is Mr. McGuire.
- How do you do, sir?

48:24.567 --> 48:25.942
I was saying that I've...

48:26.110 --> 48:28.945
This gentleman has been in theatre
a good many years.

48:29.113 --> 48:32.446
You've been in my theatre many
years too. Why don't you scram?

48:32.616 --> 48:34.941
- Of course we'll go. We...
- That's all right.

48:35.118 --> 48:37.609
You're perfectly welcome
to stay, but this guy...

48:37.787 --> 48:40.954
This guy is with us, Mr. McGuire.
We brung him.

48:41.124 --> 48:43.793
- I'm sorry.
- That's my one virtue: Nice friends.

48:43.960 --> 48:47.792
Rusty, this is Noel Wheaton of
Wheaton's Theatre. This is Mr. McGuire.

48:47.964 --> 48:50.087
- Hello. How are you?
- One side, please.

48:50.258 --> 48:53.258
We're a little crowded here.
Would you mind moving?

48:53.511 --> 48:56.049
- Forgive us.
- Make yourselves at home, will you?

48:56.222 --> 48:58.843
Look, people with clothes on.

48:59.016 --> 49:01.685
I have to get on next.
Would you excuse me? Maurine.

49:01.852 --> 49:03.975
- Coming.
- Miss Parker...

49:04.271 --> 49:07.188
- Oh, hello, Miss Jackson.
- Hello.

49:07.357 --> 49:10.477
Why didn't you tell me
you wanted somebody animated?

49:10.652 --> 49:13.190
I was just holding myself in
when I was in your...

49:13.363 --> 49:16.862
- Have you gone batty or something?
- Is it something in me...

49:17.033 --> 49:19.738
- that brings that out in people?
- Sorry.

49:20.036 --> 49:22.361
Can't we go to your
dressing room and talk?

49:22.538 --> 49:26.536
- Well, I dress with seven other girls.
- You dress with seven other girls?

49:26.709 --> 49:31.086
Yes, and they talk a lot
and get dressed and undressed...

49:32.881 --> 49:36.630
Wouldn't it be simpler if we just lay down
and let them walk over us?

49:36.802 --> 49:40.716
- I don't know why we're here anyway.
- We're offering Miss Parker a job.

49:40.889 --> 49:44.340
- Oh, but I have a job.
- Rusty, you gotta make that change.

49:44.517 --> 49:46.225
- Mr. McGuire.
- Excuse me.

49:46.394 --> 49:49.181
We are definitely in the man's way here.
Let's find...

49:49.355 --> 49:52.190
How do you feel about
selling Miss Parker's contract?

49:52.358 --> 49:54.018
Miss Parker has no contract.

49:54.193 --> 49:58.273
- No... Oh, what are we waiting for?
- I don't know. What are you waiting for?

49:58.447 --> 50:01.068
Miss Parker's free to
work for me if she wants?

50:01.325 --> 50:04.279
Miss Parker'd be free to work for you
if she wanted to...

50:04.453 --> 50:07.157
whether she'd signed a paper or not.

50:07.331 --> 50:10.830
You don't understand people
working together that way, do you?

50:11.001 --> 50:14.416
- No, I don't.
- No, you wouldn't.

50:14.671 --> 50:17.126
- Make your change, Rusty.
- Okay.

50:17.298 --> 50:22.838
- Well, I hope I see you again sometime.
- You'll see nothing but me, beautiful.

50:23.012 --> 50:27.888
That sounds very exciting,
coming from the great Noel Wheaton.

50:29.268 --> 50:32.851
You know, he said you were free to
come work for me if you wanted.

50:33.022 --> 50:37.730
- I know he did. Good night.
- Good night.

50:39.403 --> 50:43.530
- I guess my trumpet was out of tune.
- I thought I heard a sour note.

50:43.698 --> 50:46.272
Baby! You were wonderful tonight.

50:46.451 --> 50:50.151
Oh, I beg your pardon.
I mistook you for somebody else.

50:50.330 --> 50:53.449
- Glad to see you.
- So sorry.

50:53.624 --> 50:55.831
Excuse me.

50:58.087 --> 51:01.004
- Oh, wait!
- Gangway.

51:16.730 --> 51:19.730
- Busy little place tonight, wasn't it?
- Yeah, wasn't it?

51:19.899 --> 51:23.233
One had to chop one's way through
the upper crust, didn't one?

51:23.403 --> 51:25.810
Yeah, one did.

51:25.988 --> 51:27.815
Shortcuts are no good, huh?

51:27.990 --> 51:31.774
They only make you famous overnight.
That's all. No work, no nothing.

51:31.952 --> 51:35.238
Just smile at the birdie,
and boom! You're in.

51:36.123 --> 51:42.493
Name in all the papers. Big stars
sending you pretty dresses for nothing.

51:42.671 --> 51:44.498
That was terrific tonight.

51:44.881 --> 51:47.206
You bet it was terrific.

51:47.384 --> 51:49.957
Best goodbye music
I ever danced to.

51:53.431 --> 51:56.183
Yeah, tonight was really terrific.

51:56.350 --> 52:00.218
See a thing like that happen
right under your eyes.

52:00.396 --> 52:03.765
Something you wanted for someone
all their life.

52:03.941 --> 52:06.811
You haven't known me all my life.

52:06.986 --> 52:09.737
Six months then.

52:10.739 --> 52:12.150
Seven.

52:13.867 --> 52:16.073
Seven then.

52:16.995 --> 52:23.578
Seven months, three days,
four hours, 23 minutes.

52:23.751 --> 52:26.456
It was Tuesday.

52:27.588 --> 52:32.713
Long ago and far away

52:32.885 --> 52:36.585
I dreamed a dream one day

52:36.764 --> 52:42.434
And now that dream is here beside me

52:42.603 --> 52:47.644
Long the skies were overcast

52:47.816 --> 52:51.350
But now the clouds have passed

52:51.528 --> 52:57.779
You're here at last

52:57.950 --> 53:03.324
Chills run up and down my spine

53:03.497 --> 53:07.198
Aladdin's lamp is mine

53:07.376 --> 53:12.999
The dream I dreamed was not denied me

53:13.173 --> 53:15.629
Just one look

53:15.801 --> 53:19.750
And then I knew

53:20.972 --> 53:25.385
That all I longed for

53:25.560 --> 53:31.230
Long ago was you

